This is an effect from the Tiratok demo by deMarche
	from CAfE 2019
	https://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=83538

Originally for ZX Spectrum

music is by nq

This is an 88 frame animation playing on the Apple II as Mockingboard
music plays.  The frames are compressed with zx02 in 8k (8 frame) chunks.

The Tiratok devs nicely released their souce code. However I am not a z80
expert so the code is a bit dense to me.  However for this I use
their javascript prototype code, converted it to C, and then had it
dump the frames that I could import into my existing Scroll Block port.

The music is truncated a bit as the existing player only had room for 8k
of pt3 file and the original music is quite long (and large).

